SIMPLE: abort
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abort
<hw>A*bort"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*b⟦ocir⟧rt")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>abortare</ets>, fr. <ets>abortus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>aboriri</ets>; <ets>ab</ets> + <ets>oriri</ets> to rise, to be
born. See <er>Orient</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To miscarry; to bring forth young
prematurely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>To become checked in normal
development, so as either to remain rudimentary or shrink away wholly;
to become sterile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>to stop, cease, or fail prior to normal
completion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Abort
<hw>A*bort"</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*b⟦ocir⟧rt")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>to
cause (an action or process) to stop at an early stage, or before normal
completion; <as>as, to <ex>abort</ex> a rocket flight</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Abort
<hw>A*bort"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>abortus</ets>, fr.
<ets>aboriri</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An untimely birth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An aborted offspring.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aborted</ent>⟦br⟧
